The United Nations Food and AgricultureOrganization, FAO, said it approved emergency food aid worthmore than 14.3 mln dlrs for drought victims in Ethiopia.    The aid will include 30,000 tonnes of wheat and 1,200tonnes of vegetable oil for farmers in the Wollo and Illubaborregions.    FAO said it has also approved more than 1.4 mln dlrs offood aid for 8,000 families in Sri Lanka. In addition, 583,225dlrs of aid will be made available to Malawi to feed 96,700people displaced from Mozambique and a further 340,200 dlrs forcyclone victims in Vanuatu in the South Pacific. Reuter&#3;